This paper presents a system for event extraction using neural networks, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and ML. The paper also mentions the use of a corpus to train the model, which suggests that it may also fit into cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of neural networks also suggests that it may fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the ACE corpus, which is a common dataset for event extraction, suggesting that it may also fit into cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
